<subSubSection id="C31544F4C375FF9FFF3BFCCABFF57969" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BB0177FC375FF9FFF3BFCCAB80B7255" blockId="2.[136,1037,788,810]" box="[136,1037,788,810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<typeStatus id="54B4A9DDC375FF9FFF3BFCCABCBE7256" box="[136,184,788,809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Type</typeStatus>
(designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFEE3FCCABDCC7255" author="Doll, R." box="[336,458,788,810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref37377" refString="Doll, R. (1973) Revision der sect. Erythrosperma Dahlst. emend. Lindb. f. der Gattung Taraxacum Zinn. 2. Teil. Feddes Repertorium 84: 1 - 180. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19730840102" type="journal article" year="1973">Doll 1973: 2</bibRefCitation>
):— 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFE43FCCAB80E7255" authority="Handel-Mazzetti (1907: 106)" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityPageNumber="106" authorityYear="1907" box="[496,1032,788,810]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocephalum">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFE43FCCABEEE7256" box="[496,744,788,809]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Taraxacum calocephalum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFD5DFCCAB80E7255" author="Handel-Mazzetti, H." box="[750,1032,788,810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" refId="ref37719" refString="Handel-Mazzetti, H. (1907) Monographie der Gattung Taraxacum. Franz Deuticke, Leipzig &amp; Wien, xi + 175 pp. + 7 plates. [https: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / records / item / 10236]" type="book" year="1907">Handel-Mazzetti (1907: 106)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0177FC375FF9FFF3BFC86B86175ED" blockId="2.[136,1452,856,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
Plants usually medium-sized, not slender, of a ± robust habit, base with a tunic or with a few old petioles, or without tunic. Petiole winged, usually broadly winged in outer and middle leaves, not winged in later, inner leaves; leaf blade pinnatisect; lateral lobes few to numerous, usually triangular to narrowly triangular, patent to ± recurved, margin entire or (usually on interlobes) often dentate or lobulate. Capitulum usually (2.5–) 3–3.5 (–4) cm wide. Outer phyllaries usually 12–20, lanceolate to broadly ovate, long, often imbricate, appressed, loosely appressed, or less often arcuaterecurved, usually distinctly broadly or narrowly bordered, apex flat to corniculate. Ligules yellow; floret tube glabrous. Achene red, reddish brown, brown, castaneous, cinnamon or light greyish stramineous-brown, usually 
<quantity id="4CF7BA9AC375FF9FFA90FBEEB9AA7534" box="[1315,1452,1072,1099]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="4.9" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="4.3">4.3–5.5 mm</quantity>
long; body usually densely spinulose above, usually subabruptly to subgradually narrowing into a distinct cylindric (0.5–) 
<quantity id="4CF7BA9AC375FF9FFF60FBA6BD4375EC" box="[211,325,1144,1171]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
cone, spinules long and thin; beak usually 
<quantity id="4CF7BA9AC375FF9FFC94FBA6BFAE75EC" box="[807,936,1144,1171]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" unit="cm" value="1.05" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.3 cm</quantity>
. Pappus ± white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0177FC375FF9FFF0EFB42BD1A745C" blockId="2.[136,1452,856,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
Members of 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFEE8FB43BD7675C9" box="[347,368,1181,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFEE8FB43BD6A75C9" box="[347,364,1181,1206]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFE0DFB42BE5375C9" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[446,597,1180,1206]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Erythrocarpa">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFE0DFB42BE5375C9" box="[446,597,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are agamospermous, with a single exception, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFB3EFB43B91C75C9" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" baseAuthorityName="Baldacci" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[1165,1306,1180,1206]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pindicola">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFB3EFB43B91C75C9" box="[1165,1306,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. pindicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Within the distribution area of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFED2FB1FBDE075A5" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" baseAuthorityName="Baldacci" baseAuthorityYear="1899" box="[353,486,1216,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pindicola">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFED2FB1FBDE075A5" box="[353,486,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. pindicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or in its vicinity, the variation pattern of 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFC1BFB1FBFBB75A5" box="[936,957,1217,1242]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFC1BFB1FBFBF75A5" box="[936,953,1217,1242]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFC48FB1EB89475A5" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[1019,1170,1216,1242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Erythrocarpa">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFC48FB1EB89475A5" box="[1019,1170,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
follows the geographical parthenogenesis model (Hörandl 2006), and several agamospermous species are morphologically close to the variable sexual taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0177FC375FF9FFF0EFAF2BF8A773D" blockId="2.[136,1452,856,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
About 45 species are known to belong to 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFD31FAF3BE9E7439" box="[642,664,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFD31FAF3BE957439" box="[642,659,1325,1350]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFD67FAF2BF6D7439" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[724,875,1324,1350]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Erythrocarpa">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFD67FAF2BF6D7439" box="[724,875,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, occurring in the northern Mediterranean and Irano-Turanian regions, including 
<collectingCountry id="F31857EFC375FF9FFE7AFA8EBE0A7415" box="[457,524,1360,1386]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F31857EFC375FF9FFDABFA8EBE4A7415" box="[536,588,1360,1386]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Italy</collectingCountry>
, Balkan Peninsula, the Black Sea region, 
<collectingCountry id="F31857EFC375FF9FFB9AFA8EB87F7415" box="[1065,1145,1360,1386]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F31857EFC375FF9FFB01FA8FB8E47414" box="[1202,1250,1361,1387]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Iran</collectingCountry>
, and occasionally are found outside that area (the Western Carpathians, the Caucasus, 
<collectingCountry id="F31857EFC375FF9FFC18FAABBFDD74F0" box="[939,987,1397,1423]" name="Iraq" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F31857EFC375FF9FFC5BFAAAB87274F1" box="[1000,1140,1396,1422]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F31857EFC375FF9FFB30FAAAB8CD74F0" box="[1155,1227,1396,1423]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">China</collectingCountry>
). The section, both morphologically and on the basis of molecular analyses, is close to 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFC24FA47BFAB74CD" box="[919,941,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFC24FA47BFAE74CD" box="[919,936,1433,1458]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFC42FA46B89C74CD" box="[1009,1178,1432,1458]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrosperma</emphasis>
(smaller achenes, outer phyllaries usually not appressed, without border or with a less distinct border, leaf shape more complicated). Another similar but geographically remote group is 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFDDAFA3FBE787485" box="[617,638,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFDDAFA3FBE7C7485" box="[617,634,1505,1530]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFD0EFA3FB8147485" authority="van Soest (1966: 377" authorityName="van Soest" authorityYear="1966" box="[701,1042,1504,1531]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Dissecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFD0EFA3FBF1B7485" box="[701,797,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Dissecta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFC97FA3FB8147485" author="van Soest, J. L." box="[804,1042,1504,1531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="364 - 377" refId="ref39345" refString="van Soest, J. L. (1966) New species of Taraxacum from Asia I, II. Proceedings, Koniklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen, ser. C, 69 (3): 364 - 377 (I) et 378 - 388 (II)." type="journal article" year="1966">van Soest (1966: 377</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, for a more detailed information, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFF3BF9DABD217761" author="Ge, X. J. &amp; Kirschner, J. &amp; Stepanek, J." box="[136,295,1540,1566]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="270 - 325" refId="ref37572" refString="Ge, X. J., Kirschner, J. &amp; Stepanek, J. (2011) Taraxacum F. H. Wiggers. In: Wu, Z. Y., Raven, P. H. &amp; Hong, D. Y. (Ed.) Flora of China, Vols. 20 - 21. St. Louis, Missouri Botanical Garden Press &amp; Beijing, Science Press, pp. 270 - 325." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Ge 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFF1CF9DBBCE07761" box="[175,230,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), and there are also morphological links to 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFCB1F9DBBF117761" box="[770,791,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFCB1F9DBBF157761" box="[770,787,1541,1566]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFCE6F9DABFB17761" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[853,951,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Scariosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFCE6F9DABFB17761" box="[853,951,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Scariosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFC4DF9DBB8BB7761" authorityName="Sonck" authorityYear="1989" box="[1022,1213,1540,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panhellenicum">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFC4DF9DBB8BB7761" box="[1022,1213,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. panhellenicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the species closest to intersectional intermediates, e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFDADF9F7BF86773D" authority="Dahlstedt (1926: 6)" authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityPageNumber="6" authorityYear="1926" box="[542,896,1575,1602]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graecum">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFDADF9F7BE9D773D" box="[542,667,1577,1602]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. graecum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFD11F9F6BF86773D" author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[674,896,1575,1602]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref37200" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1926) Uber einige orientalische Taraxacum-Arten. Acta Horti Bergiani 9 (1): 1 - 36 + 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1926">Dahlstedt (1926: 6)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0177FC375FF9FFF0EF992BDC77640" blockId="2.[136,1452,856,2071]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
Since 1985, we re-defined 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFE56F993BDFC7719" box="[485,506,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFE56F993BDF07719" box="[485,502,1613,1638]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFD8BF992B87C7719" authority="(Dahlstedt 1909: 172) Dahlstedt (1921: 37)" authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityPageNumber="37" authorityYear="1921" baseAuthorityName="Dahlstedt" baseAuthorityPageNumber="172" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[568,1146,1612,1638]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Obliqua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFD8BF992BE927719" box="[568,660,1612,1638]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Obliqua</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFD12F992BF827719" author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[673,900,1612,1638]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="167 - 179" refId="ref37127" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1909) Nya skandinaviska Taraxacum-arter. Botaniska Notiser 1909: 167 - 179. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 211121  page / 507 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1909">Dahlstedt 1909: 172</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFC21F992B87C7719" author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[914,1146,1612,1638]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref37169" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1921) De svenska arterna av slaktet Taraxacum. I. Erythrosperma, II. Obliqua. Acta Florae Sueciae 1: 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1921">Dahlstedt (1921: 37)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, another related and similar group, originally including only two agamospermous species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFCEFF9AFB9AD77F4" authority="(Fries 1814: 14) Dahlstedt (1905: 152" authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityYear="1814" baseAuthorityName="Fries" baseAuthorityPageNumber="14" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[860,1451,1648,1675]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obliquum">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFCEFF9AFBFE077F5" box="[860,998,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. obliquum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFC4BF9AEB8A277F5" author="Fries, E. M." box="[1016,1188,1648,1674]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" refId="ref37484" refString="Fries, E. M. (1814) Novitiae florae suecicae, Vol. 1. Berling, Lundae, 22 pp." type="book" year="1814">Fries 1814: 14</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFB04F9AEB9AD77F4" author="Dahlstedt, H." box="[1207,1451,1648,1675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="145 - 172" refId="ref37085" refString="Dahlstedt, H. (1905) Om skandinaviska Taraxacumformer. Botaniska Notiser 1905: 145 - 172. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 210848  page / 1 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1905">Dahlstedt (1905: 152</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
&amp; 164) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFEAAF94BBEDC77D0" authority="Raunkiaer (1906: 256)" authorityName="Raunkiaer" authorityPageNumber="256" authorityYear="1906" box="[281,730,1684,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyglossum">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFEAAF94BBDCD77D1" box="[281,459,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. platyglossum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFE66F94ABEDC77D0" author="Raunkiaer, C. C." box="[469,730,1684,1711]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" refId="ref38501" refString="Raunkiaer, C. C. (1906) Dansk Exkursions-Flora [...]. Gyldendalske Boghandel Nordisk Forlag, Kjobenhavn og Kristiania, 286 pp." type="book" year="1906">Raunkiaer (1906: 256)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but now understood as a group centered around the sexual 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFA24F94BBDC877AD" authority="Reuter (1861: 4)" authorityName="Reuter" authorityPageNumber="4" authorityYear="1861" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyrenaicum">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFA24F94BBD0D77AD" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. pyrenaicum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFEA0F967BDC877AD" author="Reuter, G. F." box="[275,462,1720,1747]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" refId="ref38528" refString="Reuter, G. F. (1861) Catalogue des graines recueillies en 1861 et offertes en echange par le Jardin botanique de Geneve. Impr. Ramboz &amp; Schuchart, Geneve, 4 pp." type="book" year="1861">Reuter (1861: 4)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and covering not only the two coastal species but also a number of similar plants from the Western Alps and adjacent areas, mainly in 
<collectingCountry id="F31857EFC375FF9FFD12F903BEF77788" box="[673,753,1757,1783]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">France</collectingCountry>
. Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFCF1F903B8207789" authority="Hand." authorityName="Hand." box="[834,1062,1756,1782]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquilonare">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFCF1F903BFDF7789" box="[834,985,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T. aquilonare</emphasis>
Hand.
</taxonomicName>
-Mazz. in Dalla-Torre &amp; Sarnthein (1912: 687), included in 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFE2AF8DFBDA97665" box="[409,431,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFE2AF8DFBDAC7665" box="[409,426,1793,1818]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F6CFCC375FF9FFE5FF8DEBE857665" authorityName="Handel-Mazzetti" authorityYear="1907" box="[492,643,1792,1818]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Erythrocarpa">
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFE5FF8DEBE857665" box="[492,643,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Erythrocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by us in 1985 (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E6A8EC375FF9FFC98F8DEB8637664" author="Kirschner, J. &amp; Stepanek, J." box="[811,1125,1792,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" pagination="111 - 134" refId="ref37808" refString="Kirschner, J. &amp; Stepanek, J. (1985) ' Taraxacum hoppeanum' and its allies. (Studies in Taraxacum 4). Preslia 57: 111 - 134. [http: // www. preslia. cz / archive / Preslia _ 57 _ 1985 _ 111 - 134. pdf]" type="journal article" year="1985">Kirschner &amp; Štěpánek 1985</bibRefCitation>
), is now treated as a marginal member of 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFEBAF8FBBD187641" box="[265,286,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFEBAF8FBBD1C7641" box="[265,282,1829,1854]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
