are mostly widespread and grow at lower elevations, often with an ability to spread to sites influenced by human activities, the European 
<emphasis id="B97BCB6DC375FF9FFB0DF84FB8D576D5" box="[1214,1235,1937,1962]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<collectionCode id="ED1E8FBAC375FF9FFB0DF84FB8C976D5" box="[1214,1231,1937,1962]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">T</collectionCode>
